  "bio_raw": "She is a dedicated academic professional with extensive experience in teaching, research, and consultancy. She served as a Lecturer at Primeasia University from December 26, 2025, to January 13, 2025, where she effectively contributed to the academic and professional growth of students. Prior to that, she gained valuable experience as a Research Assistant at Khulna University, enhancing her skills in data analysis, academic writing, and collaborative research.\nFrom 2016 to 2018, she worked as a Research Consultant for the project titled “By Feeding the World Will be Fed? Food Security and Well-being in Shrimp and Prawn Aquaculture in Bangladesh.” Driven by a deep passion for academia and research, she is dedicated to advancing impactful studies, nurturing intellectual growth, and contributing to innovative solutions that promote sustainable development.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Applied Statistics, Machine Learning, Public Health Analytics, Demographic Studies, Quantitative Research Methods, Business Analytics, Probability and Statistical Theory, Data-Driven Decision Making."
  ],
